\f0\fs58 \cf0 Neapolitan Easter Pie
\f1\fs36 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf0 Yield 
\b0\fs38 Makes one 12-inch pie\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs50 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl1
\f1\fs42 \cf0 		4 ounces spring wheat\
		2 cups milk\
		2 tablespoons unsalted butter\
		Pinch of salt\
		12 ounces whole-milk ricotta (about 1 1/2 cups)\
		3/4 cup sugar\
		Pastry Cream (recipe below)\
		Sweet Dough (recipe below)\
		All-purpose flour, for work surface\
		1 large egg, lightly beaten, for egg wash\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Place wheat in a medium bowl. Add enough water to cover by 2 inches. Refrigerate overnight. Drain, and transfer to a medium saucepan. Add milk,1 cup water, butter, and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer, and cook until tender, about 1 hour. Drain, and spread on a baking sheet. Let cool, about 30 minutes.\
{\listtext	2.	}Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a medium bowl, stir together ricotta and sugar. Add cooled wheat, and pastry cream. Stir to combine.\
{\listtext	3.	}Remove the larger piece of dough from refrigerator. On a lightly floured surface, roll into a 16-inch circle, about 1/8 inch thick. Fit into a 12-by-2-inch cake pan. Pour filling into the crust; set aside. On a lightly floured surface, roll out remaining piece of dough, 1/8-inch-thick. Cut into 3/4-inch lattice strips. Weave the lattice strips over the filling, pinching edges to seal. Crimp edges as desired.\
{\listtext	4.	}Brush top of pie evenly with egg wash. Transfer to oven, and bake, rotating halfway through, until crust is golden and filling is bubbling, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.\
