\f0\fs54 \cf0 Pastry Cream
\f1\fs26 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs32 \cf0 Yield 
\b0\fs34 Makes about 2 1/2 cups
\fs42 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\fs50 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl1
\f1\fs42 \cf0 		3 large egg yolks\
		1/2 cup all-purpose flour\
		6 tablespoons sugar\
		2 cups whole milk\
		1 vanilla bean split and scraped\
		Pinch of salt\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 	\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\fs42 \cf0 	1.  Prepare an ice bath; set aside. In a medium bowl, whisk together egg yolks, flour, and sugar; set aside. In a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, combine milk, vanilla bean, and salt. Bring just to a boil.\
{\listtext	2.	}Using a measuring cup or a ladle, slowly pour about 1 cup of the hot milk mixture into the egg-yolk mixture, whisking constantly. Pour mixture back into saucepan, and cook over low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until thick 1 to 2 minutes.\
	3. Strain through a fine mesh sieve into a medium bowl set over the ice bath. Let stand, stirring occasionally, until cool. Place a piece of plastic wrap directly on the surface of the pastry cream. Transfer to refrigerator until cold, at least 1 hour, and up to overnight. Just before using, remove from refrigerator, and whisk to soften slightly.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa280\ql\qnatural
