\f0\fs52 \cf0 Sweet Dough
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\b\fs32 \cf0 Yield 
\b0\fs34 Makes enough for one 12-inch lattice-topped pie
\fs42 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\fs50 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl1
\f1\fs42 \cf0 		1 1/2 pounds (just under 5 cups) all-purpose flour\
		2 teaspoons baking powder\
		1 pinch of salt\
		1 cup (2 sticks) unsalted butter, room temperature\
		1 cup sugar\
		Grated zest of 1 orange\
		3 large eggs\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\fs42 \cf0   1.  In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt; set aside.\
{\listtext	2.	}In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat the butter and sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Beat in the orange zest. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating until fully incorporated after each addition.\
{\listtext	3.	}Reduce speed to low, and beat in the dry ingredients. Turn the dough out onto a work surface. Divide dough, making sure one piece is slightly larger than the other. Place each piece of dough on a sheet of plastic wrap. Flatten, to form two discs. Wrap, and refrigerate at least 1 hour before using.
